article.headline: Providence 76, Yale 63
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) -- Freshman Sharaud Curry scored 20 of his career-high 25 points in the second half while classmate Geoff McDermott added 18 points and nine rebounds to lead Providence to a 76-63 win over Yale on Thursday night. Caleb Holmes and Dominick Martin each scored 13 for Yale (5-5). Curry shot 10-of-14 from the floor, including 8-of-11 in the second half, when the Bulldogs never got closer than five. The Friars (5-4) had eight steals and converted 18 Yale turnovers into 22 points, while the Bulldogs shot just 36 percent. McDermott scored 12 first-half points to spark Providence to a 31-26 halftime lead, after a first half that featured five lead changes and four ties. The Bulldogs outrebounded the Friars 26-12 in the half and took nine more shots to keep the game close.
